cs.DM, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.GT 

The paper deals with topics related to discrete mathematics, logic, graph theory, and distributed computing. The use of bisimulation and 2-variable counting logic suggests that it belongs to cs.DM and cs.LO. The discussion of color refinement and equitable partitioning suggests cs.CC and cs.DS. Finally, the focus on graph isomorphism and universal covers suggests cs.GT.
